{
  "stem": "24409.7",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He didn't take the main road.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He went on a side road.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he looked at his list, that I am on the list.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was not on the list, so he let us pass.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I was afraid that the conditions are changed, and they might not let anybody in, in spite of the visas.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I had visas.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I told you, I think, how I got the visas-- through the British visa which I had.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I went to Milan.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And in Milan was a group, a revisionist group.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the man in charge was a Major [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Kareski. ?] And I knew him superficially, but he knew me, also superficially.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But we knew each other well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I came to him and told him, I have to get into Switzerland, because only from there can I go on organizing things.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Now it was a thing which I don't think I wrote about it, in I had a passport, which I had really gotten in Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And on this passport, this German official wanted to be very nice, and he didn't stamp the J into it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But it said, [INAUDIBLE] shows that I was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But the red J was not in it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So he says, I said, I need the J.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And he says, I'll have one done by a printer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he has put a J into-- I has got the J, red J into my name, because I was afraid if I come to Switzerland, if I'm a German, I'm-- a citizen of a warring party, and they might not let me in.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was better to be a Jew, a refugee, than to be a German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "That's what I figured.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
